From: CyreneClang <cyrene@cyreneclang.dev>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 06:44:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] nsan: fix std::array redefinition with GCC 14 libstdc++

nsan.h includes <math.h> after sanitizer_redefine_builtins.h (via
sanitizer_internal_defs.h). With GCC 14's libstdc++, <math.h> in C++
mode transitively includes <bits/stl_pair.h> which defines
std::array, conflicting with the `using array = ...` alias in
sanitizer_redefine_builtins.h.

Define SANITIZER_COMMON_REDEFINE_BUILTINS_IN_STD before the sanitizer
include to skip the conflicting aliases, since nsan legitimately needs
standard C headers.

Signed-off-by: CyreneClang <cyrene@cyreneclang.dev>
---
 compiler-rt/lib/nsan/nsan.h | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/compiler-rt/lib/nsan/nsan.h b/compiler-rt/lib/nsan/nsan.h
index 896e5379dfc3..71633b0f3877 100644
--- a/compiler-rt/lib/nsan/nsan.h
+++ b/compiler-rt/lib/nsan/nsan.h
@@ -12,6 +12,7 @@
 #ifndef NSAN_H
 #define NSAN_H
 
+#define SANITIZER_COMMON_REDEFINE_BUILTINS_IN_STD
 #include "sanitizer_common/sanitizer_internal_defs.h"
 
 using __sanitizer::sptr;
-- 
2.46.0
